# Project Conventions

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router), TypeScript (strict), Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui
- PostgreSQL + Prisma ORM, NextAuth.js v5
- Zustand (client state), TanStack Query (server state)
- Zod for all validation

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript strict mode. No `any` types.
- Use Server Components by default. Add 'use client' only when needed (hooks, event handlers, browser APIs).
- File naming: kebab-case for files and folders, PascalCase for React components.
- Imports: use @/ path alias for all project imports.

## Database
- Always use the `db` client from `@/lib/db`.
- Never use raw SQL — always use Prisma queries.
- All mutations must validate input with Zod schemas from `@/lib/validators/`.

## API Routes
- All API routes return `ApiResponse<T>` type from `@/types`.
- Use try/catch with consistent error handling.
- Validate request body with Zod. Return 400 for validation errors, 401 for unauthorized, 404 for not found, 500 for server errors.

## Components
- Use shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui/`.
- Domain components go in `@/components/{domain}/` (tickets, workflows, tasks, etc.).
- Shared components go in `@/components/shared/`.

## State Management
- Zustand stores in `@/stores/` for client-side state.
- TanStack Query for server data fetching and caching.
- Custom hooks in `@/hooks/`.
